  "text": "Theorem 1.1. For (B 3 , g), g ∈ M, there exist C, C 0 > 0 such that the resolvent R(λ) (defined in (1.1)) extends holomorphically from Im λ < 0 to {λ ∈ C : Im λ < C log |λ| + C, | Re λ| ≥ C 0 } as an operator from L 2 comp (B 3 ) to L 2 loc (B 3 ). See Figure 1 . The resonance free regions in the AHM setting have been actively studied in the last two decades. For general AHMs (not necessarily non-trapping), Guillarmou [CITATION_1] obtained a resonance free region {λ ∈ C : Im λ < e −C|λ| , | Re λ| > C > 0}, which is exponentially close to the real axis. It is also proved in [CITATION_2] that there exist resonance free strips of fixed width under additional assumptions that the manifold is non-trapping with constant negative curvature near the infinity. This is improved by Vasy [CITATION_3] to resonance free strips of any width, i.e. for any C 1 there exists a C 2 such that there is no resonance in",
